<br>
2 HQ Tundra Kodiak Pelts + 2 HQ Cougar Skins = 1 Coldain Hunter's Blanket (recommended tailoring skill is 86, but I've done several with a skill of only 35.....go figure).....done in a regular old large sewing kit<br>
<br>
1 Skinning Stone + Wooly Rhino Horn + 1 HQ Walrus Skin = Coldain Hunter's Knife (combined in a forge....trivs at about 80 skill in smithing)<br>
<br>
Non-tradeskill items are: Rygorr Invasion Plans, Roderick's Head, A key to free the coldain warrior in EW.<br>
<br>
ALL ITEMS CAN BE FOUND IN EW! All animal parts (pelts, horn) come off the respective animals in Eastern Wastes. The Skinning Stone is a ground spawn in EW. The Invasion Plans come off the Rygorr Messenger, but if you dont' feel like camping them, usually the people at the fort will either give you a set or sell to you cheap. Roderick is a bit more of a pain. You have to wait for the Rygorr Emmisary to spawn, and make sure no one touches him till he gets outside the fort, then makes his way back inside to the Crystal Caverns zone area. Once there, he will spawn Roderick outside the fort at the CC exit area. You'll want to loot both his head, and his dirk (the dirk is used in the 9th ring quest). <br>
<br>
Once you have all these items, I'll be glad to help form a crack team of Federalies and get you from your 1st to your 8th ring. If you need help doing the combines, let me know and I'll gladly try them for you and MQ the first 4 rings. Once we complete all of this, TA DA! You will have your Velium (8th) Coldain Ring. Stats are 8ac 8str 8MR, right click effect of an 8 point Damage Shield. Now you have the information, so let's get those rings done and make our Fed tanks that much better=).<br>
<br>
Nueinx Justlight, 55th Paladin<br>
Ealic Lifegiver, 54th Cleric<br>
